<div class="vision"> B-LINK VISION</br> <h2>We envision a better connected well informed Ugandan citizenry so as to facilitate discovery, participation and co-creation between people, government and private sector.</h2></div>

<div class="mission" align="center"> B-LINK MISSION</br> <h2>At BLINK we partner to reduce disparities in information accessibility and to build a resilient and active citizenry of people who are informed to fight poverty, diseases, hunger; promote civics education and democracy in the country.</br>The BLINK will partner with public, private, school, college and universities/institutions and Non-governmental organizations (NGOs) in the country and other international organizations of working in cooperation with the education, university, training, business and medical communities. This initiative seeks to serve Uganda citizens with the assistance of all levels of government. </br>The goal of the BLINK is to assist information users in seeking, navigating and using electronic information through the effective management and delivery of electronic resources to Ugandans. The services provided are geared towards assisting Ugandans at all ages to learn about, find and locate the information they need.
</h2></div>

<div class="Content">The most Ugandan task before us is to get medical and health knowledge to those most in need of the knowledge. James Grant, UNICEF 1993...</div>
      
